sentence.text: Genes involved in tissue development, differentiation, and oncogenesis such as protein refolding, HES5, negative regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II, diet induced thermogenesis, positive regulation of transcription, DNA-templated, GATA6, ALX3, and P4HTM were hypermethylated in both RMS cell lines and primary samples, implicating aberrant DNA methylation in the pathogenesis of rhabdomyosarcoma.
